{"id":26459,"date":"2018-05-24T13:35:01","date_gmt":"2018-05-24T09:35:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=26459"},"modified":"2019-05-09T14:58:06","modified_gmt":"2019-05-09T10:58:06","slug":"warning-iftar-no-excuse","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/05\/24\/warning-iftar-no-excuse\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Fasting: Warning to those who break fast without excuse"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>While I was sleeping, two men came to me and took me by the arm to a rough mountain. They said: Climb up. I said: I am unable to do so. They said: We will make it easy for you. I climbed until I was halfway up the mountain and I heard loud voices. I said: What are these loud voices? They said: This is the howling of the people of Hellfire. Then, they departed with me until I saw some people hanging by their heels, the corners of their mouth split open and running with blood. I said: Who are these? They said: They are those who would break their fasting before it was complete<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Sunan al-Kubra\u0301 7396<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e <strong>\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0646\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0645\u064c \u0625\u0650\u0630\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0627\u0646